4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the crime of manslaughter is
6 a Class B felony which may be committed by: (i)
7 reckless murder; (ii) heat of passion murder; (iii)
8 knowingly furnishing a controlled substance containing
9 fentanyl to another which is the proximate cause of the
10 recipient's death; or (iv) operating a motor vehicle or
11 vessel while under the influence and causes the death
12 of another.
13 This bill would amend the third option for the
14 crime by providing that the crime is committed if the
15 person furnishes any controlled substance to another
16 which is the proximate cause of the recipient's death.
17 This bill would also increase the penalty for
18 such violation.
19
20
21 A BILL
22 TO BE ENTITLED
23 AN ACT
24
25 Relating to crimes; to amend Section 13A-6-3, Code of
26 Alabama 1975, as last amended by Act 2026-64, 2026 Regular
27 Session, to provide that the crime of manslaughter is
28 committed if a person furnishes any controlled substance that
